This paper is about capacity allocation and scheduling in wireless networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses mathematical optimization algorithms, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT) or mathematical optimization (cs.MA). The paper also mentions Pareto efficiency, which is a concept in game theory and economics, and could fall under systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of proportional fairness in multi-channel multi-rate wireless networks, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) as wireless networks are often used for multimedia applications.
